\begin_layout Abstract
We list all possible point groups for 
\begin_inset Formula $1,2,3,4$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 atoms as well as for 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-atom molecules with specified formulas.
 For each point group, we give examples of molecules of each size and formula
 if they are known, and hence we determine the yet-to-be discovered molecules
 with under 5 atoms for each point group.
 We establish a small set of principles that can be used for proofs about
 the possibility or impossibility for a molecule of a certain size and/or
 formula to have a point group symmetry.
\end_layout

