\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang british
One might wonder why, despite group theory being applied to molecules for
 about 100 years (Bethe 1929), the questions that are being addressed in
 this paper do not appear to have been answered yet.
 Indeed we have asked all living authors of () if they have ever come across
 a list of all possible point groups for a 4-atom (tetraatomic) system,
 and in all cases we were explicitly told that they were unaware of such
 a list, or we received no response at all.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang british
Our need for answers to the question in the present paper's title, arose
 during other work.
 GW100 (MJ van Setten 2015) is a dataset of 100 systems (95 molecules and
 5 atoms)
